.TH SS_SCREENKEY "1" "December 2025" "202602020740-git" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
ss_screenkey \- Screenkey wrapper for displaying keystrokes
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ss_screenkey
[\fI\,OPTIONS\/\fR] [\fI\,start\/\fR|\fI\,stop\/\fR|\fI\,toggle\/\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B ss_screenkey
is a wrapper script for screenkey, which displays keystrokes on screen. It provides easy control for starting, stopping, and toggling screenkey display.
.PP
The script is useful for screencasts, demonstrations, and tutorials where showing keystrokes is helpful.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-help
Display help message with usage information and available options
.TP
.BR \-\-config
Generate or regenerate user configuration file with default settings
.TP
.BR \-\-version
Show script version information and exit
.TP
.BR \-\-options
Display all available command-line options
.TP
.BR \-\-debug
Enable debug mode with verbose output and command tracing (set -x)
.TP
.BR \-\-raw
Disable colorized output for plain text display
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B start
Start screenkey
.TP
.B stop
Stop screenkey
.TP
.B toggle
Toggle screenkey on/off
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B ss_screenkey start
Start displaying keystrokes
.TP
.B ss_screenkey toggle
Toggle keystroke display
.SH FILES
.TP
.B ~/.config/myscripts/ss_screenkey/settings.conf
User configuration file for ss_screenkey preferences
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success
.TP
.B 1
General error
.TP
.B 3
Screenkey not found
